        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks for notes on <hi rend="italic">Cypripedium</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Platanthera hookeri</hi>, which is really beautiful and quite a new case.</p> 
            <p>His son, George, has been observing the insect fertilisation of orchids.</p> 
<p>CD has been crossing peloric flowers of <hi rend="italic">Pelargonium</hi>, but doubts he will get good results with respect to sterility of hybrids.</p>  
<p><hi rend="italic">Rhexia glandulosa</hi> does not appear to be dimorphic. <hi rend="italic">Lythrum</hi> is trimorphic.</p> 
        </abstract>
